<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus possilensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="possilensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus possilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron, 1882a: 178-179. ♀. Syntypes (assumed). Type locality: Possil Marsh near Glasgow, Scotland. Lectotype ♀ hereby designated, labelled: &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM. 1.573&quot; [printed], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus possilensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="possilensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus possilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cam.&quot;, &quot;Cameron 96-76. [printed] Possil&quot; [handwritten], &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM. [printed] 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus possilensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="possilensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus possilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Cameron 1882)&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Lectotypus" lsidName="Lectotypus" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Lectotypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[printed] 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus possilensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="possilensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus possilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron, 1882 [handwritten in block letters] M.Heidemaa design. [printed]&quot; [red]. Most of the abdomen missing. Ovipositor preparation apparently lost, but probably figured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cameron, P" journalOrPublisher="Ecological Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B28" refString="Cameron, P, 1882a. A Monograph of the British Phytophagous Hymenoptera. (Tenthredo, Sirex and Cynips, Linne.). Volume 1. Ray Society, London 340 pp. [21 plates]" title="A Monograph of the British Phytophagous Hymenoptera. (Tenthredo, Sirex and Cynips, Linne.). Volume 1. Ray Society, London 340 pp. [21 plates]" year="1882 a">Cameron (1882a</bibRefCitation>
: plate XIX, fig. 8). BMNH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Probably a parthenogenetic species: no male has ever been recorded. The only known Fennoscandian record is from Sweden: 1♀ [labelled as 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.] 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Resarö">&quot;Resaroe</normalizedToken>
Waxholm / 6 1915&quot;, leg. R. Malaise, NHRS. New to the Swedish fauna.
</paragraph>
